// Man page for pack
manPack="PACK(1)                          X Shell Manual                          PACK(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    pack - Pack or repack libraries and routers
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>pack -a</b>
    <b>pack -m</b> [-y]
    <b>pack -c</b> [-y]
    <b>pack -r</b> [-i IP]
    <b>pack -s</b>
    <b>pack -t</b>
    <b>pack --check</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    The pack utility packages libraries and routers for portable deployment.
    It enables crypto encryption/decryption and maintains libraries in the
    /payload/data folder for use on target systems. X automatically manages
    metaxploit.so and crypto.so in data; other libraries require manual placement.

    Target system libraries take precedence over packed versions. Use -y flag
    to skip removal when packing metaxploit.so or crypto.so.

    <color=#e4ff34>*** Requires root access for crypto encrypt/decrypt ***</color>
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>-a</b> - Pack All
      Pack all libraries: crypto, metaxploit, and router.

    <b>-m</b> [-y] - Pack Metaxploit
      Pack metaxploit.so library. Use -y to skip removal confirmation.

    <b>-c</b> [-y] - Pack Crypto
      Pack crypto.so library. Use -y to skip removal confirmation.

    <b>-r</b> [-i IP] - Pack Router
      Pack router. Optionally specify IP to pack specific router.

    <b>-s</b> - Pack Appliance
      Pack smart appliance libraries.

    <b>-t</b> - Pack Traffic
      Pack traffic management libraries.

    <b>--check</b> - List Packed Items
      Display all currently packed items in /payload/data.
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Pack All Libraries</color>
    <b>pack -a</b>
    Pack crypto, metaxploit, and router

    <color=#e4ff34># Pack Individual Items</color>
    <b>pack -m</b>
    Pack metaxploit.so with confirmation

    <b>pack -m -y</b>
    Pack metaxploit.so skipping removal confirmation

    <b>pack -c -y</b>
    Pack crypto.so skipping confirmation

    <b>pack -r</b>
    Pack current router

    <b>pack -r -i 192.168.1.1</b>
    Pack specific router at IP address

    <b>pack -s</b>
    Pack appliance libraries

    <b>pack -t</b>
    Pack traffic libraries

    <b>pack --check</b>
    List all packed items
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>0day</b>, <b>lms</b>"